Q54. Design question: why BankVault methods need PIN every time?
A: Because private fields alone aren’t enough — methods must authorize each sensitive action. Encapsulation stores secrets; method logic enforces access policy.
________________________________________
Q55. 30-second encapsulation summary for interviews.
A: Encapsulation hides internal state and exposes a safe interface. In Python use _/__, getters/setters or @property, and put validation in methods. It’s by convention (bypassable via mangling), but essential for clean, maintainable, rule-enforcing OOP design.
